article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 65, Morehead State 63
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Michael Brock hit a 3-pointer with 44 seconds left and Eastern Kentucky held on for a 65-63 win over Morehead State Thursday night. Morehead State (1-12, 0-7 Ohio Valley Conference) took a 63-59 lead with 1:51 left on a bucket by Quentin Pryor. Whitt connected on a three-point play 29 seconds later, setting up Brock's game winner for Eastern (7-9, 4-3). A last attempt by Morehead's Pryor hit the back of the rim and fell off. The Colonels trailed by as many as 11 points in the second half. Eastern was led by Matt Whitt's 22 points, who scored 13 of 15 scored in one second-half stretch. Jason McLeish had 18 for the Colonels. Pryor scored 19 to lead Morehead State, Cordaryl Ballard added 13, and Quinton Smith and Shaun Williams scored 12 each.
